OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FBy Daniel Boal, ITV News Producer
OL,8,FSir Keir Starmer's already tough week
OL,9,Fmay get even worse after reports that
OL,10,FHealth Secretary Wes Streeting is
OL,11,Fprepared to resign and start a formal
OL,12,Fleadership contest against the prime
OL,13,Fminister.
OL,15,FStarmer has been fighting to stay in
OL,16,Fthe top role since Labour's
OL,17,Fcatastrophic election losses last
OL,18,Fweek, which have since resulted in the
OL,19,Fresignations of four ministers and
OL,20,Fcalls from more than 90 MPs for the PM
OL,21,Fto quit.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FThe electorate has spoken, and it has
OL,7,Fbeen open season on Starmer's
OL,8,Fleadership ever since.
OL,10,FAnd, while no one has officially
OL,11,Fbroken ranks to challenge him and his
OL,12,Fposition, rumblings inside the
OL,13,FParliamentary Labour Party (PLP) have
OL,14,Fthrown out several contenders.
OL,16,FBut how can a leadership contest be
OL,17,Ftriggered, and who are the key
OL,18,Fplayers? ITV News explains.
OL,20,FHow could a leadership contest be
OL,21,Ftriggered?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FOver the weekend, MP Catherine West
OL,7,Fbriefly became the most talked-about
OL,8,Fwoman in politics when she started
OL,9,Fcalling for the PM to step down.
OL,11,FWhile she has since softened her
OL,12,Fposition and won't be challenging the
OL,13,FPM, the momentum behind her call is
OL,14,Fundeniable.
OL,16,FTo mount a leadership contest, 20% of
OL,17,Fthe party's MPs ` or 81 colleagues `
OL,18,Fneed to back a replacement candidate
OL,19,Ffirst.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FITV News has tracked more than 93 MPs
OL,7,Fwho either want Starmer gone with
OL,8,Fimmediate effect or for him to set out
OL,9,Fa timeline for his departure.
OL,11,FWhile more than 81 MPs have called for
OL,12,Fthe prime minister to go, that doesn't
OL,13,Fnecessarily translate into support for
OL,14,Fthe names being mooted as potential
OL,15,FStarmer alternatives.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FOnce the leadership contest is
OL,7,Ftriggered, other candidates can join
OL,8,Fthe race if they also have the backing
OL,9,Fof at least 81 MPs. Starmer, however,
OL,10,Fwill automatically be on the ballot
OL,11,Fpaper.
OL,13,FHe would also continue in the role
OL,14,Fwhile the contest was in progress.
OL,16,FIn Labour's 126-year history, there
OL,17,Fhas never been an official leadership
OL,18,Fchallenge mounted at a sitting prime
OL,19,Fminsiter.
OL,21,FThen what happens?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FOnce a candidate has 81 backers, the
OL,7,FNational Executive Council (NEC) `
OL,8,FLabour Party's ruling body ` makes
OL,9,Farrangements for a full vote with
OL,10,Fparty members.
OL,12,FThere is also no formal limit on
OL,13,Fcandidates who can put themselves
OL,14,Fforward to replace Starmer, but they
OL,15,Fmust have the requisite backing.
OL,17,FAnd, MPs can only throw their support
OL,18,Fbehind one candidate at a time - in
OL,19,Fpractice, capping the opposition
OL,20,FStarmer could face if the contest is
OL,21,Ftriggered.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FAnother challenge facing those wanting
OL,7,Fto unseat Starmer is the deadline that
OL,8,Fmay be imposed by the NEC.
OL,10,FMPs will likely only have around a
OL,11,Fmonth to shore up their supporters,
OL,12,Fmaking it almost impossible for
OL,13,FGreater Manchester Mayor Andy Burnham
OL,14,Fto mount a challenge if it were
OL,15,Ftriggered immediately. But more on him
OL,16,Flater.
OL,18,FHow does the vote work?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FThe decision-making rests with party
OL,7,Fmembers and affiliated trade union
OL,8,Fsupporters - who rank candidates in
OL,9,Forder of preference.
OL,11,FIf a candidate secures over 50% of the
OL,12,Ffirst preference votes, they are
OL,13,Fdeclared the winner and will become
OL,14,Fthe new leader of the Labour Party, or
OL,15,Fin Starmer's case, remain in his job.
OL,17,FFailing that, the candidate who places
OL,18,Flast is eliminated and the voters who
OL,19,Fput them as their number one choice
OL,20,Fwill have their votes moved to their
OL,21,Fsecond choice candidate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FThe process continues until one
OL,7,Fcandidate secures more than 50% of the
OL,8,Fvotes cast.
OL,10,FWhy is a union vote important too?
OL,12,FLabour as a political party is
OL,13,Fformally linked to several trade
OL,14,Funions such as Unite the Union,
OL,15,FUnison, and GMB. Each provides
OL,16,Ffunding, campaign support, activists
OL,17,Fand as a result has sway over policy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FLeadership candidates often rely on
OL,7,Fthe resources provided by unions,
OL,8,Fmaking them one of the most important
OL,9,Fstakeholders in a Labour leadership
OL,10,Fcontest.
OL,12,FWho could stand against Starmer and
OL,13,Fmake their bid to be prime minister?
OL,15,FThe man who looks most likely to
OL,16,Fchallenge Starmer's premiership
OL,17,Fdirectly is Health Secretary Wes
OL,18,FStreeting, with reports indicating
OL,19,Fthat he could resign as a Cabinet
OL,20,Fminister and launch his own ticket as
OL,21,Fsoon as Thursday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FWes Streeting
OL,8,FBefore today, Streeting had appeared
OL,9,Freluctant to make the first move
OL,10,Fagainst Starmer.
OL,12,FBut after a 16-minute meeting with the
OL,13,FPM at Downing Street on Wednesday
OL,14,Fmorning, sources told Political Editor
OL,15,FRobert Peston, the health secretary
OL,16,Fcould step away from his role as soon
OL,17,Fas tomorrow.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FHis reluctance to move first has made
OL,7,Fthings difficult, mostly due to the
OL,8,Ffact that many of the 92 MPs calling
OL,9,Ffor the PM to quit are his supporters.
OL,11,FHis team is insisting they are doing
OL,12,Fso without instruction from Streeting,
OL,13,Fbut as Peston previously reported, few
OL,14,Fin parliament believe that to be
OL,15,Fcredible or relevant.
OL,17,FAndy Burnham
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FFor those on the soft left of Labour,
OL,7,FGreater Manchester Mayor Andy Burnham
OL,8,Fis widely seen as the leading
OL,9,Fcandidate.
OL,11,FThis is in part due to a quality that
OL,12,Fis seemingly becoming increasingly
OL,13,Frare within Labour - he is popular.
OL,15,FA recent YouGov poll conducted by The
OL,16,FTimes said that 27% of voters think he
OL,17,Fwould do a good job as PM, compared to
OL,18,F22% who think he would do poorly, and
OL,19,F48% of Labour voters think he would do
OL,20,Fa good job.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FBut the road for Burnham from
OL,7,FManchester to Westminster is riddled
OL,8,Fwith hurdles.
OL,10,FFor one, Burnham isn't an MP.
OL,12,FAnd two, Starmer has previously
OL,13,Fblocked Burnham from standing using
OL,14,Fhis influence over the NEC - a move
OL,15,Fthat former deputy leader Angela
OL,16,FRayner called a "mistake" earlier this
OL,17,Fweek.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31215
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FTo challenge Starmer, Burnham must
OL,7,Ffirst find a seat. There he has two
OL,8,Fpaths; there are two by-elections
OL,9,Fcoming up in Scotland, as the SNP's
OL,10,FStephen Flynn and Stephen Gethins
OL,11,Fvacate their seats.
OL,13,FChallenging in either seat would be a
OL,14,Ftall order for Burnham and would
OL,15,Freally test his "King in the North"
OL,16,Fmoniker.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31216
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FFar more likely is him needing one of
OL,7,Fhis Labour colleagues to step down, so
OL,8,Fhe can participate in a by-election,
OL,9,Fwin a seat, and then secure enough
OL,10,Fsupport within the party to run as an
OL,11,Falternative to Starmer.
OL,13,FThere is another route to the top for
OL,14,FBurnham, which would involve Starmer
OL,15,Ffalling on his own sword.
OL,17,FMany within the party have called for
OL,18,Fhim to set out a departure timeline,
OL,19,Fgiving Burnham the time to manoeuvre
OL,20,Fhimself into a seat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
