OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FAngela Rayner
OL,8,FNot so far in the distant past, Angela
OL,9,FRayner was seen by many as the future
OL,10,Fof the Labour Party.
OL,12,FStarmer's former deputy prime minister
OL,13,Fand housing minister had a staunch
OL,14,Fbase within the PLP.
OL,16,FHowever, after a recent run-in with
OL,17,Fthe HMRC over her tax affairs, and her
OL,18,Frivals appearing as better options in
OL,19,Fthe polls - Rayner may instead choose
OL,20,Fto throw her support behind a soft-
OL,21,Fleft candidate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31218
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FEarlier this week, Rayner appeared to
OL,7,Fthrow her support behind Burnham,
OL,8,Fcalling Starmer's decision to block
OL,9,Fhim from running as an MP last year a
OL,10,F"mistake".
OL,12,FEd Miliband
OL,14,FEnergy Secretary and former Labour
OL,15,FParty leader Ed Miliband has been a
OL,16,Fname thrown around as a potential to
OL,17,Freplace Starmer.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31219
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1778785872
OL,3,CHow would a Labour leadership contest
OL,4,Cwork?
OL,6,FSources close to Miliband have denied
OL,7,Fthat he is preparing to run, but The
OL,8,FTimes reported that the Energy
OL,9,FSecretary will enter the race as the
OL,10,Fcandidate for the soft-left if
OL,11,FStreeting triggers a contest.
OL,13,FA source close to Miliband denied the
OL,14,Fsuggestion ` in quotes first given to
OL,15,Fthe newspaper ` saying: "This is
OL,16,Fmischief making. It is categorically
OL,17,Funtrue that Ed told Cabinet colleagues
OL,18,Fthat he was preparing to stand in case
OL,19,Fof a contest."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
